Bedrock is multi-licensed. Per-file licensing is declared, machine-readably, in REUSE.toml
(https://reuse.software) and verified by `reuse lint`; the full license texts are in LICENSES/.
The summary below is for humans; REUSE.toml is authoritative.

Three buckets
-------------
1. CC BY-NC-SA 4.0  (LICENSES/CC-BY-NC-SA-4.0.txt, mirrored at LICENSE-CC-BY-NC-SA)
   The mathematical development and the user-facing prose, plus the brand marks:
     - src/**            the Cubical Agda development
     - docs/**           the trilingual user documentation
     - README.md         the (trilingual) project readme
     - site/static/assets/  the brand marks (favicon, inline README mark, social banner)

2. OFL-1.1  (LICENSES/OFL-1.1.txt, mirrored at LICENSE-OFL)
   The self-hosted third-party web fonts under site/static/fonts/ (EB Garamond, Inria Sans,
   JuliaMono). Not Bedrock's to relicense; each font's own license text is co-located there.

3. AGPL-3.0-only  (LICENSES/AGPL-3.0-only.txt, mirrored at LICENSE-AGPL)  -- the default
   Everything else: all first-party code and configuration (scripts, .github/**, Makefile,
   bedrock.agda-lib), the site front-end (site/static/bedrock.css, site/static/bedrock.js,
   scripts/render-site.py, site/template.html), the prose developer docs (dev/**, AGENTS.md,
   CONTRIBUTING.md, NOTICE, this file), and the vendored 1lab front-end under site/vendor/1lab/
   (Copyright (C) 2021 Amelia Liao and contributors; the catch-all default folds it in).

The three LICENSE-* files in the repository root duplicate the LICENSES/ texts so GitHub's
license detection (which does not read the REUSE LICENSES/ directory) lists all three. See
NOTICE for third-party attributions and the AGPL section 13 corresponding-source statement.
